    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Recondition - Inspect and Measure Valve Guides
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Inspect and Measure Valve Guides</title>
        <figure id="f3350013370" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/h08003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Clean valve guides</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1319" count="1">Clean valve guides with soap, water, and a nylon brush.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position an inspection light at the bottom of valve guide bores. Inspect bores for burning
                or cracks. Replace any damaged valve guides.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350013371" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/h08004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measure valve guide with ball gauge</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f3350013372" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5420.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measure Ball gauge with micrometer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure inside diameter of each valve guide with a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">ball gauge or small hole gauge set and an
                    outside micrometer
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001303"/>.
            </para>
            <para>If valve guide bore, taper, or out of round exceeds
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_339.xml" xrefid="t335001301">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001301"/>, replace the valve guide.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure valve guides within 0.64 mm (0.025 in) of each end and 90 degrees from crankshaft
                center line. Record measurements. Determine valve stem-to-guide running clearance after doing "
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_324.xml" xrefid="s1321">Inspect and Measure Valves</hotlnk>" procedure
                <xref refid="s1321"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
